The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, October 19, 2002 				 Minister says no to hosting each other
																								Bhopal: There is no possibility in the near future of India and Pakistan playing cricket matches against each other in either of the two countries, sports minister Vikram Verma said Friday.																								India can, however, meet Pakistan in multi-nation tournaments not played either in India or Pakistan, Verma added.																								We have no objection if India plays against Pakistan in such tournaments at selected venues, he said.																								The minister clarified selected venues are the ones chosen by the ICC. (PTI)
